    "causal_summary": "The graph-metadata backfill CLI ignores a positional folder and defaults to the repo-wide root, then refreshes every collected folder, so a single-packet intent silently walks the whole tree and dirties unrelated sessions. Collection also admits candidates the writer rule canClassifyAsGraphMetadataPath would reject, and one corrupt folder aborts the whole run. The z_* exclusion policy is split across backfill, memory-index, code-graph, and the description scanner whose local skip list omits z_*. This phase adds an explicit scoped boundary that refreshes one packet by default with broad mode behind a default-off all flag, makes collection match the writer rules and isolate per-folder failures, and introduces one authoritative z_* exclusion helper with a descriptions.json guard, every behavioral fix behind a default-off flag or a grandfather report mode and the by-design z_archive memory inclusion preserved through a separate generatedMetadata policy.",
